(1) A deed of arrangement to which this Act applies shall include any instrument of the classes hereinafter mentioned whether under seal or not— (a) made by, for or in respect of the affairs of a debtor for the benefit of his creditors generally ; (b) made by, for or in respect of the affairs of a debtor who was insolvent at the date of the execution of the instrument for the benefit of any three or more of his creditors; otherwise than in pursuance of the law for the time being in force relating to bankruptcy.
